    "Body": " Role: Digital Finance Transformation Consultant Salary: Up to ?56,000 depending on skills & experience Location: London Travel: Up to 100% Welcome to Accenture, one of the world's leading providers of consultancy services where innovation and high performance is delivered. We are leading the way in helping our clients harness the power of digital to transform the finance function and its role within our clients. At Accenture we are seeking professionals who want to make a real difference and have the passion and experience to bring digital technologies and new operating models to our clients and help them achieve results. As part of the 6,000+ Accenture Consulting professionals in our global community, you will join the Digital Finance team where we play a central role in working with some of the world\u2019s most dynamic global companies, responsible for helping CFOs address some of the top challenges faced today. As a Digital Finance Transformation Consultant, you will: Lead and/or support project teams engaged in a successful delivery of a wide range of Digital Finance initiatives aligning finance with business strategy in support of the broader organization\u2019s future vision Help develop Digital Finance strategies by assessing a client\u2019s business challenges/needs/gaps, diagnosing the root problems and recommending an approach leveraging Accenture assets Help create strategies and blueprints that define end-to-end finance processes (e.g., Procure to Pay, Order to Cash, Record to Report) and harness the power of robotic process automation, machine learning, and/or artificial intelligence to accelerate transaction processing. Partner with client and Accenture project team to blueprint and design end-to-end Cloud ERP and Enterprise Analytics business solutions for our clients to transform the Finance function Identify and support business development initiatives; participate in all aspects of the proposal development process Work across the global Digital Finance practice to share lessons learned and best practices Maintain an understanding of advancements in technology and innovations which are happening across digital, analytics, the CFO ecosystem, and the broader marketplace What we are looking for: We are looking for candidates that excel in working in a client facing environment with proven delivery and functional skills. Candidates should be able to approach Finance & Accounting complexities in an informed, structured and innovative way. Candidates for the role must be able to demonstrate an understanding in one or more of the following key areas within Finance and Accounting: Finance Function \u2013 strong understanding of the end to end Finance Processes and Financial Reporting functions: Record to Report, Order to Cash, Procure to Pay and other Finance Processes FP&A Reporting Risk and Treasury Reporting General Ledger Standardisation, Architecture and Strategy Chart of Accounts re-design Finance Systems: Strong knowledge of finance management systems and technical ERP environments (SAP, Oracle, Workday), experience in implementing ERP cloud solutions (S4Hana, Oracle Cloud Financials); experience with other Finance technologies such as Blackline, Anaplan, Analytic Tools, etc. Data Fluency in Finance \u2013 ability to evaluate and comprehend data and analytics reporting functions. Experience with platforms such as Tableau, Power BI and QlikView is valued but not essential; Intelligent Automation \u2013 experience and ability to understand core finance capabilities and challenges that relate to AI, Robotics, Blockchain and other areas within Digital Finance. What experience we are looking for: Highly collaborative, team-oriented consensus builder with strong stakeholder management skills and the ability to build continuing relationships with our clients Deep understanding and experience of Operational Excellence levers and the practical application of process excellence (Lean, Scrum), organisation efficiency, service and footprint models Track record of communicating and influencing at different levels, including strong presentation and \u2018story telling\u2019 skills Proven track record of successful project delivery Strong facilitation, and data gathering skills Good Excel and PowerPoint skills are essential Good understanding of Finance and Procurement functions Professional Qualification (ACA, CIMA, ACCA, CFA) is preferable Ability to meet travel requirements Additional Experience Knowledge of blockchain, big data, cognitive analytics, data analytics and artificial intelligence and the impact on Finance applications and operating models Experience in cost saving initiatives as a result of more streamlined data provided within automation of finance reporting Design Thinking concepts \u2013 able to brainstorm, problem-solve and present ideas using a variety of design thinking methods available What\u2019s in it for you? All our consulting professionals receive comprehensive training covering business acumen, technical and professional skills development in the latest techniques such as design thinking, data visualization, AI and robotics. You will also have opportunities to hone your functional skills and expertise in an area of specialization. We offer a variety of formal and informal training programs at every level to help you acquire and build specialized skills faster. Learning takes place both on the job and through formal training conducted online, in the classroom, or in collaboration with others. The sheer variety of work we do, and the experience it offers, provide an unbeatable platform from which to build a career. A focus on your strengths and continuous coaching from senior colleagues enable fast-paced progression with competitive rewards. You\u2019ll benefit from working alongside Accenture experts who are solving some of the biggest industry challenges with innovative thinking and cutting-edge tools. On top of this, we have an extensive benefits package which includes 30 days\u2019 vacation per year, gym subsidies, private medical insurance and 3 extra days leave per year for charitable work of your choice, allowing you to also have opportunities to make a difference to the communities in which we work and live. What are the next steps? If this sounds like the ideal role, career and company for you, click below to apply. About Accenture Accenture is a leading global professional services company, providing a broad range of services and solutions in strategy, consulting, digital, technology and operations. Combining unmatched experience and specialized skills across more than 40 industries and all business functions \u2014 underpinned by the world\u2019s largest delivery network \u2014 Accenture works at the intersection of business and technology to help clients improve their performance and create sustainable value for their stakeholders. With 505,000 people serving clients in more than 120 countries, Accenture drives innovation to improve the way the world works and lives. Visit us at www.accenture.com. Accenture is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all sections of society and does not discriminate on grounds of race, religion or belief, ethnic or national origin, disability, age, citizenship, marital, domestic or civil partnership status, sexual orientation, or gender identity, or any other basis as protected by applicable law. Closing date: 6th March 2020 Accenture reserves the right to close the role prior to this date should a suitable applicant be found. ", 
